data.content: Hi, this is Ava calling on behalf of Penn Medicine Talent Acquisition Team. You've applied for our Certified Nursing Assistant or Patient Care Technician roles. Do you have time to discuss your interest in the position now?
Great! I want to let you know that I’m an AI recruiter representing Penn Medicine, here to assist with the initial screening process. Shall we proceed?
Excellent I'll ask you questions and gather information for your application. Your responses will be recorded and shared with a recruiter who will review your answers.  Does that sound good?
Alright, let's begin. What Employment Type are you looking for?  Full Time, Part Time or Per Diem?
If offered employment, how soon would you be able to start?
Is there a preferred Penn Medicine Hospital or a location in Philadelphia that you are most interested in?
This position is based out of 800 Spruce St, Philadelphia, PA. Is this a good location for you?
Can you verify your education/certifications/licensures with a physical copy that is complete and current?
Are you authorized to work lawfully in the United States for Penn Medicine (University of Pennsylvania Health system)?
Will you now or in the future require (UPHS) sponsorship to employ you?
Have you ever been employed by Penn Medicine Health System or its affiliates?  If “yes”, where and when and what was your title?
How did you hear about Penn Medicine? Was it through Penn Medicine Career Page, another online source, Linked In, Indeed, or anything else?
Were you referred by a current Penn Medicine employee? If so, what is their name?
Have you ever been a Penn Medicine volunteer, contractor through a staffing agency or temporary employee?
Have you recently applied to any other opportunities at Penn Medicine and, if so, are you in the interview process for any of these roles?
What specialty interests you and where do you see yourself long-term within your professional career?
Please provide details on your current and/or past work history.
